  "target_response": {
    "text": "Strain is a running tally of cardiovascular load for the day, scored on a 0 to 21 scale where the top end means a near-maximal day — it climbs with time spent at elevated heart rate, so it measures effort dose, not fitness. Today's strain of 15.3 is a big day by your own recent pattern: your 7-day average strain is 11.8, so today clearly outpaces a typical day from your week. That squares with the 68 min run you logged, where your heart rate averaged 152 bpm. High isn't bad on its own — strain only tells you the size of the dose. What matters is whether tomorrow's recovery inputs absorb it; a hard day followed by solid sleep is exactly how training is supposed to look.",
